problem_statement:
Subclass RuntimeException in StandardSchedulerClient for better error handling
Due to `StandardSchedulerClient` throwing plain `RuntimeException` instances there is no way to distinguish (and possibly ignore) exceptions other than by doing string matching of the supplied message:
```
        public void cancel(TaskInstanceId taskInstanceId) {
...
            if (execution.isPresent()) {
                if (execution.get().isPicked()) {
                    throw new RuntimeException(String.format("Could not cancel schedule, the execution with name '%s' and id '%s' is currently executing", taskName, instanceId));
                }
...
            } else {
                throw new RuntimeException(String.format("Could not cancel schedule - no task with name '%s' and id '%s' was found.", taskName, instanceId));
            }
        }
```
Almost the same is done in `reschedule()`, except for slightly different message wording.

Did you consider having `TaskInstanceAlreadyRunningException` and `TaskInstanceNotFoundException` runtime exception classes? The messages can stay the same in case someone is already doing string matching for that purpose.

